The surface topography of the nanoscale electrode after each immobilization step is illustrated in Fig. 6
                         using AFM microscopy. The changes in the surface were monitored through roughness measurements based on the micrograph images obtained. Specifically, the root mean square average of height deviation from the mean image data plane (Rq) and the arithmetic average of the absolute values of surface height deviations from the mean plane (Ra) were recorded (Table 1
                        ).
